This doesn't compile, so my recommendation would be to remove dead code and only add it when it is needed.


```
./util/result.h:53:69: error: call to implicitly-deleted copy constructor of 'const result_tests::NoCopy'
    T value_or(const U& default_value) const { return has_value() ? value() : default_value; }
                                                                    ^~~~~~~
test/result_tests.cpp:74:27: note: in instantiation of function template specialization 'util::Result<result_tests::NoCopy>::value_or<int>' requested here
    BOOST_CHECK_EQUAL(obj.value_or(1), 5);
                          ^
test/result_tests.cpp:14:26: note: copy constructor of 'NoCopy' is implicitly deleted because field 'm_n' has a deleted copy constructor
    std::unique_ptr<int> m_n;
                         ^
```

